items.name: smart-event-manager
items.description: A CLI-based Smart Event Manager built using Python and OOP. Features include event scheduling, conflict detection, admin controls, email reminders via Excel, recurring events, undo, analytics, and ASCII timeline. Designed for ACM recruitment to showcase real-world coding, modularity, and CLI design.

items.name: E-English-
items.description: E++ is a proof of concept “programming language” that uses AI to convert plain English instructions written in .epp files into executable Python code, which it then runs automatically. It demonstrates the potential of writing code in natural language and having it interpreted into functional programs.
